-- Gold, Silver Futures in New York Drop for Second Day as U.S. Dollar Gains
-- B y   G l e n y s   S i m
-- 2012-02-05T23:04:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-05/gold-silver-futures-in-new-york-drop-for-second-day-as-u-s-dollar-gains.html
Gold for April delivery dropped for a
second day on the Comex in  New York , falling as much as 0.6
percent to $1,729.30 an ounce, before trading at $1,730 an ounce
at 7:02 a.m. Singapore time. Cash gold was little changed at
$1,727.40 an ounce.  March-delivery silver also declined for a second day,
losing as much as 0.3 percent to $33.635 an ounce, and last
traded at $33.66 an ounce. Spot silver was little changed at
$33.67 an ounce.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Glenys Sim at 
 gsim4@bloomberg.net  